Egg group - MONSTER / GRASS

The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.
A Grotle that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater well. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.
Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there. Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.
